itsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?=
title=3DSynthetic_division&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit=
 section: For non-monic divisors"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-ed=
itsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>With a little prodding, the expanded technique may be generalised even f=
urther to work for any polynomial, not just <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Monic_polynomial" title=3D"Monic polynomial">monics</a>. The usua=
l way of doing this would be to divide the divisor <span class=3D"mwe-math-=
element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-=
math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org=
/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle g(x)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>g</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle g(x)}</annota=
tion>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/c6ca91363022bd5e4dcb17e5ef29f78b8ef00b59" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:4.255ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle g(x=
)}"></span> with its leading coefficient (call it <i>a</i>):
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e h(x)=3D{\frac {g(x)}{a}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>h</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mi>g</mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mi>a</mi>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle h(x)=3D{\frac=
 {g(x)}{a}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/3db4459a1d63c8773bb13c64870fde8480a621f1" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; width:12.668ex; height:5.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle h(=
x)=3D{\frac {g(x)}{a}}}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>then using synthetic division with <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-m=
ath-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a=
11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/Ma=
thML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle h(x)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>h</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle h(x)}</annota=
tion>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/02c07825dae28705df03d15daeb8844d49c4dbd4" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:4.478ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle h(x=
)}"></span> as the divisor, and then dividing the quotient by <i>a</i> to g=
et the quotient of the original division (the remainder stays the same). Bu=
t this often produces unsightly fractions which get removed later and is th=
us more prone to error. It is possible to do it without first reducing the =
coefficients of <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><s=
pan class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display:=
 none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\dis=
playstyle g(x)}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
